description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you currently hold either a Foundation Degree in Health and Social Care (FdSc) or the BSc (HONS) Health and Social Care Degree? Do you enjoy the challenge of scrubbing for complex technical cases within a supportive well led team? An exciting opportunity has arisen for us to recruit a Band 4 TAP to strengthen our Thoracic and UGI team, based at the City Campus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and progressive person committed to the development of yourself and our team, supporting both our Thoracic and Upper GI services. You will be fully supported to scrub and circulate for a wide range of simple and complex surgical cases as well as develop new skills to assist during endoscopic procedures such as POEM interventions. We also have an established robot surgery programme. We currently work regularly in four different operating theatres per week, each with its own challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting opportunity will require the successful applicant to demonstrate excellent clinical scrub standards, achieved through experience gained in a range of scrub procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team value band 4 practitioners and you will be integrated into the team to support productive and more efficient ways of working with an emphasis on patient care and safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a flexible attitude to work and be able to work as part of a mulitdisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work 37.5hr flexibly between Monday and Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits to our department are encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this opportunity please contact Alan Storrow, Team Leader on 0115 9691169 x55775.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alan.Storrow@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
